// =============================================================================
// AERawIcons — PASTE-AND-GO icon registry (the low-friction path). [v1.1.4 RAWICONS]
//
// The easiest way to add an icon. Unlike AEFillIcons (which wants pre-cleaned
// 512x512 inner path content), AERawIcons takes the *raw SVG source exactly as
// copied* from SVGRepo, game-icons.net, Iconify, etc. — wrapper <g> scaffold,
// odd viewBox, hardcoded fill and all. It is normalized once, on first use, by
// _aeNormalizeRawSVG() (see below CyberIcons' fill helpers): the SVGRepo
// bg/tracer groups are dropped, the icon carrier is unwrapped, every solid
// fill/stroke is swapped to currentColor (so ThemeForge drives the color), and
// any viewBox other than 0 0 512 512 is uniformly scaled + centered into a 512
// canvas. The result is cached into AEFillIcons under the same key, so it then
// renders through the exact same fill path as everything else.
//
// HOW TO ADD ONE (the whole job):
//   1. Copy the icon's full <svg>...</svg> source.
//   2. Paste it as a backtick string under a new key here.
//   3. Use that key anywhere an icon name is accepted — a map node's `icon`
//      field, an entity icon, $.svg('key'), getCyberIconHTML('key'),
//      createCyberIcon('key'), or a theme override. Done. No reformatting.
// TO SWAP: rename the key, or move a source string to a different key.
//
// PRECEDENCE (see _aeIconRenderKind): theme override → CyberIcons (stroke) →
// AEFillIcons (hand-tuned fill) → AERawIcons. So a raw entry is a safe additive
// layer — it never shadows a same-named stroke or hand-tuned fill icon. If you
// WANT a raw icon to win a name a stroke icon already owns, give it a distinct
// key (e.g. `teleportUser`, not `teleport`) and reference that key.
//
// Colors: solid fills/strokes become currentColor. fill="none" and url(#...)
// gradient refs are left untouched, so two-tone / gradient icons keep detail.
// Need a fixed second color? Hand-tune it in AEFillIcons instead.
//
// Seed set below (v1.1.4): torch, bullets, candle, campfire, crystalBall,
// dice1–dice6, fizzingFlask, teleportUser, bigMushroom, fangs, footsteps,
// spider, pentacle, flask, ironCrown, battleMech, ship, corset, crenelCrown,
// evilTower, femaleLegs. (Their source viewBoxes span 32 / 33.867 / 128 / 512
// — all normalized to 512 automatically. "littleMushrooms" was omitted: it
// already exists as a hand-tuned AEFillIcons entry.)
// =============================================================================
