// SECTION 3b — PER-THEME ICON RESOLUTION LAYER
// Additive on top of CyberIcons — no existing call site or theme changes.
// A theme only needs to list the icon KEYS it wants to replace; anything
// absent falls through to the shared CyberIcons set unchanged. Both icon
// renderers (getCyberIconHTML for HTML strings, createCyberIcon for DOM
// elements) consult this before falling back, so overriding a key like
// 'mapPin' or 'user' re-themes it everywhere at once: map nodes, pickers,
// the roster grid, and the Party Hub button.
//
// TO ADD A THEME'S ICON SET: add a 'theme-yourtheme': { key: '<path .../>' }
// entry to AE_THEME_ICONS below. Path data follows the same 24x24 viewBox,
// stroke-based convention as CyberIcons (see PART 0.6 above).
// =============================================================================
